The Murang&rsquo;a government will disburse 2,000 bags of maize to 30,000 people who face starvation.Governor Mwangi Wairia said each of the 5,000 families will receive 10kg of maize.Worst hit areas are Makuyu, Kambiti, Kimorori, Ithanga, Kakuzi, Gaturi and Kambirwa. Wairia addressed leaders from the areas on Tuesday at the Murang&rsquo;a Teachers&rsquo; Training College.He said they will mostly target the disabled, orphans and aged people who do not have anyone to care for them.&ldquo;As the leadership of the county, we cannot afford to have any death caused by hunger. That is why we have decided to start distributing relief food,&rdquo; Wairia said.&ldquo;We have agreed with local leaders that each of the affected location will receive 100 bags of maize,&rdquo; he said.Wairia said President Uhuru Kenyatta directed both the national and county governments to work together and ensure no life is lost.He said the food will be accounted for to ensure only the targeted people get it.Wairia said the county will distribute seeds in March to 75 per cent of small-scale farmers.